# Copy to .env (gitignored). NEVER commit real secrets.
# The app itself is fully on-device — no cloud parse tier, no sign-in — so it
# needs NO EXPO_PUBLIC_* values to run. The keys below are DEV-TOOLING ONLY:
# they configure the parse-eval harness (evals/, `npm run eval:*`), which is
# never bundled or shipped. The eval scripts auto-load this file.

# --- Parse-eval harness (evals/) — dev tooling, never ships ---
# The BYOK cloud tiers grade the REAL shipping raw-fetch engines
# (src/features/ai/engines/{anthropic,openai}.ts) against evals/dataset.jsonl.
# Each is a real API call to the provider (costs money) and is report-only —
# no key set => that tier skips cleanly (green), never blocks a build.

# Claude tier: `npm run eval:cloud`
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional model override (default claude-haiku-4-5):
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# OpenAI tier: `npm run eval:openai`
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Optional model override (default gpt-4o-mini):
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# Apple Foundation Models tier (`npm run eval:fm`) needs no key — it shells out
# to the local Swift probe (macOS 26 + Apple Intelligence). FM_PROBE_PATH is
# set by the eval:fm script itself; no entry needed here.
